OL,3,CJohnny Mercer accuses Labour opponent
OL,4,Cof lying about military service
OL,6,F"I was a minister in the department,
OL,7,Fhe never has. If he's going to lie
OL,8,Fabout that, what else is he going to
OL,9,Flie about?
OL,11,F"I respect everyone's service,
OL,12,Fparticularly in this city, but you do
OL,13,Fnot lie about it."
OL,15,FLabour has criticised his comments,
OL,16,Fwith shadow defence secretary John
OL,17,FHealey urging Mr Mercer to "do the
OL,18,Fright thing" and "withdraw his deeply
OL,19,Fdisrespectful remarks".
